# Homepage dashboard (gethomepage)

Live dashboard YAML lives in **hdc-private** (`packages/services/homepage/homepage/services.yaml`). Public hdc holds examples, icon assets, resolvers, and lint.

## Every service tile needs an icon

- Prefer [dashboard-icons](https://github.com/homarr-labs/dashboard-icons) names in YAML: `immich.png`, `n8n.png`.
- When no dashboard-icons entry exists, vendor PNG under `packages/services/homepage/homepage/icons/` and reference `/icons/<file>.png` in `services.yaml`.
- Update `homepage/icons/README.md` with upstream source URL.

## Service widgets

When [gethomepage](https://gethomepage.dev/widgets/services/) documents a widget for an app **and** hdc deploys that app on the dashboard:

1. Add entry to [`homepage-widget-catalog.mjs`](../../packages/services/homepage/lib/homepage-widget-catalog.mjs).
2. Add resolver under `packages/services/homepage/lib/homepage-*-widget.mjs` and wire in [`homepage-widget-env.mjs`](../../packages/services/homepage/lib/homepage-widget-env.mjs).
3. Enable `homepage.<id>_widget` in homepage `config.json` (schema in `tools/hdc/schema/homepage.config.schema.json`).
4. Add `widget:` block in `services.yaml` using `{{HOMEPAGE_VAR_*}}` placeholders — **never** paste secrets in YAML.
5. Document vault keys in `.env.example` and [`packages/services/homepage/README.md`](../../packages/services/homepage/README.md).

Proxmox and Pi-hole follow the same pattern; see README sections.

## Lint before maintain

```bash
node tools/hdc/cli.mjs run service homepage query -- --lint
```

`homepage maintain` runs the same lint and fails on errors (missing icon, enabled widget without YAML block, orphan widget, missing vendored `/icons/` file).

## Checklist for new tiles

- [ ] `icon` set (dashboard-icons or vendored `/icons/…`)
- [ ] Widget added if gethomepage supports it and secrets/config documented
- [ ] `query --lint` passes
- [ ] `homepage maintain` after YAML or config changes
